    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:h --remote-wait` says \"Not yet supported by Nvim\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`--remote-wait` is supported by Nvim.\r\n\r\n(Can't use `neovim --remote` as git editor, since the invocation immediately terminates after launching the remote instance, yielding \"Aborting commit due to empty commit message.\")\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "My proposal in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/18414 is that `--remote` always waits (blocks until return). And if one wants asynchronous (immediate return) behavior, prepending `:&` to a command opts-into that behavior.\r\n\r\nThis means we have one single `--remote` thing, not all the other `--remote-foo` junk from Vim.",
